# Performance & Security

## Performance
- Rendering is highest impact: default to Server Components (zero client JS); each `'use client'` adds to the bundle — keep Client subtrees as small as possible.
- Images: `<Image>` from `next/image`, never bare `<img>` for content. `priority` only for above-the-fold/LCP; remote hosts in `images.remotePatterns`.
- Fonts: `next/font` only (Geist set up in root layout). No `@font-face` or CDN `<link>` — prevents FOUT/CLS.
- Code-split heavy, non-initial Client Components with `next/dynamic` (editors, charts, maps, conditional modals/drawers); `ssr: false` only if it can't run on server; provide a `loading` skeleton.
- Stream: wrap slow async RSC in `<Suspense>`; add `loading.tsx` to segments with slow fetches.
- Re-renders: don't add `useMemo`/`useCallback` pre-emptively (profile first); avoid new object/array literals to memoized children; keep RTK Query args stable to hit cache.
- Bundle: audit with `ANALYZE=true npm run build`; keep route first-load JS < 150KB gz; avoid full-library imports (use sub-path/native).
- Core Web Vitals: LCP < 2.5s (priority hero images, RSC to avoid client waterfalls), INP < 200ms (small Client subtrees, no main-thread blocking in handlers), CLS < 0.1 (explicit `width`/`height` on media, skeletons reserve space).

## Security
- Auth token in `localStorage` (read in `src/services/baseApi.ts`) is an XSS risk; planned migration to `httpOnly` cookies. Until then: no other secrets/PII in `localStorage`; keep the existing pattern — no parallel token storage.
- Env: `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` is bundled to the client — never put secrets/keys there (base URL is fine). Non-public vars are server-only (RSC, Route Handlers, Server Actions, `next.config.ts`).
- Validate before any DB/API call, using only parsed data: Server Action body (Zod, always), Route Handler body + query (Zod/manual, always), client mutation (Zod via RHF before dispatch), RSC URL params (coerce + bounds-check). Validate auth on every protected Route Handler.
- XSS: avoid `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`; if unavoidable, sanitize user HTML with `DOMPurify` (client-side).
- CSP: set security headers in `next.config.ts` for prod (`X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`).
- Logging: never log tokens/passwords/PII or raw credential-bearing bodies; treat RSC server logs as sensitive; remove all `console.log` before merging to main.
